WEBVTT

00:02.535 --> 00:04.336
Well,
could be an acute o.S.A.

00:04.338 --> 00:07.139
I don't have sleep apnea.
How do you know?

00:07.141 --> 00:08.507
'cause my airways
aren't constricted,

00:08.509 --> 00:10.309
Oxygen levels in my blood
haven't dropped,

00:10.311 --> 00:12.111
And I don't snore...
Much.

00:12.113 --> 00:13.479
[ clears throat ]

00:13.481 --> 00:15.714
I just wish
you were sleeping more.

00:15.716 --> 00:17.082
Baby, I slept.

00:17.084 --> 00:18.717
For like three months
I slept.

00:18.719 --> 00:20.319
[ chuckles ]
I'm good till like 2020.

00:20.321 --> 00:21.487
[ siren wailing ]

00:21.489 --> 00:22.654
Thank you.

00:22.656 --> 00:24.189
What about a new bed?

00:24.191 --> 00:25.257
New bed?

00:25.259 --> 00:27.092
Yeah.
We've had that thing forever.

00:27.094 --> 00:29.328
Eh, if it ain't broke,
don't fix it.

00:29.330 --> 00:30.662
[ chuckles ]
so, what do you say?

00:30.664 --> 00:32.064
New bed, fresh start.

00:32.066 --> 00:33.699
Mm...
Could be a good thing.

00:33.701 --> 00:36.168
Woman: <i>...Pourquoi?</i>
<i>I'm thinking</i>
<i>pillow top --</i>

00:36.170 --> 00:38.070
<i>Hello? Hello?</i>
<i>And queen, not king,</i>

00:38.072 --> 00:39.438
Because
you're basically sleeping...

00:39.440 --> 00:42.074
<i>Regardez-moi! Pourquoi?</i>
<i>Regardez-moi!</i>

00:42.076 --> 00:43.275
<i>Je vous en prie.</i>

00:43.277 --> 00:44.743
<i>Qu'est-ce qui se passe?</i>

00:44.745 --> 00:46.211
Hey, charlie.

00:46.213 --> 00:47.679
Am I bed-shopping
alone here?

00:47.681 --> 00:50.249
[ indistinct conversations ]

00:50.251 --> 00:52.051
Um...

00:52.053 --> 00:53.452
Where'd you go?

00:53.454 --> 00:54.787
Pillow top.

00:54.789 --> 00:57.256
We were talking about
p-pillow top, right?

00:57.258 --> 00:59.792
[ dragonette's "giddy up"
playing ]

01:02.796 --> 01:04.730
¶ I get up a half-empty cup

01:04.732 --> 01:06.498
¶ check my pulse
just to feel the beat ¶

01:06.500 --> 01:08.400
¶ I've got to get goin',
put my trousers on ¶

01:08.402 --> 01:10.202
¶ keep the dead weight
off of my feet ¶

01:10.204 --> 01:12.204
¶ I'm thinkin',
"who can I call on?" ¶

01:12.206 --> 01:14.406
¶ but everyone's all gone off
at the end of the week ¶

01:14.408 --> 01:16.475
¶ I'm feelin'
as sour as a gallagher ¶

01:16.477 --> 01:18.477
¶ for reasons unknown,
should I have stayed home? ¶

01:18.479 --> 01:21.113
¶ no, giddyup

01:21.115 --> 01:22.815
¶ come on, giddyup

01:22.817 --> 01:24.616
Gentlemen.

01:24.618 --> 01:25.818
Joel goran.
How are you?

01:25.820 --> 01:27.419
Doug wilkens.
Nice to meet you.

01:27.421 --> 01:30.656
This is mark forsythe,
ricki's coach.

01:30.658 --> 01:32.858
Hey, man.
How are you?

01:36.830 --> 01:38.497
Your daughter's
a hell of a player, mate.

01:38.499 --> 01:39.765
Yeah.

01:39.767 --> 01:41.767
I've actually only ever seen her
on television,

01:41.769 --> 01:44.236
But she's got
amazing ground speed.

01:44.238 --> 01:46.572
20 winners in yesterday's
third-round match.

01:46.574 --> 01:48.607
I saw that.
Only two unforced errors, right?

01:48.609 --> 01:50.309
Yeah,
and all on a bum knee.

01:51.845 --> 01:54.546
Listen, doctor.
I hear that you're the best.

01:54.548 --> 01:57.850
Well, my daughter deserves
nothing but the best.

01:57.852 --> 02:00.385
Well,
I'm glad you called.

02:00.387 --> 02:03.155
Ohh!

02:03.157 --> 02:06.225
¶ come on, man, giddyup

02:06.227 --> 02:08.560
She tweaked it going for
too much on a key second serve.

02:08.562 --> 02:10.496
I should've taken something
off the first,

02:10.498 --> 02:12.331
Kicked it out wide.
But you didn't.

02:12.333 --> 02:14.399
You pulled out the big gun,
you got yourself into trouble,

02:14.401 --> 02:15.868
And then you tweaked
the damn knee again.

02:15.870 --> 02:17.236
So, these incision scars
you have here --

02:17.238 --> 02:18.604
These are from
previous scopes, right?

02:18.606 --> 02:20.372
Doug: Yeah, she's been having
cartilage scraped

02:20.374 --> 02:22.241
Since the year
she turned pro.

02:22.243 --> 02:23.408
Yeah, I got to be honest
with you --

02:23.410 --> 02:24.743
It feels like
there's more damage.

02:24.745 --> 02:26.245
[ chuckles ]
so what?

02:26.247 --> 02:28.614
Shot of cortizone --
right as rain, right?

02:28.616 --> 02:30.149
Uh, I won't know
the extent of the damage

02:30.151 --> 02:31.483
Unless I get more imaging.

02:31.485 --> 02:33.285
Well, she's playing
in the quarterfinals

02:33.287 --> 02:34.553
This afternoon.
Yeah,
that's not a good idea.

02:34.555 --> 02:35.888
We don't want
to mess with her mechanics

02:35.890 --> 02:37.489
In the middle
of the tour.

02:37.491 --> 02:40.425
Yeah, there's significant
swelling around her patella.

02:40.427 --> 02:43.162
This is the busiest part
of the tour, doctor,

02:43.164 --> 02:45.297
You know,
balancing everybody's schedules.

02:45.299 --> 02:46.798
Do you have any idea
what that's like?

02:46.800 --> 02:49.168
I do, yeah, actually.

02:49.170 --> 02:50.469
Look, um, you called me.

02:50.471 --> 02:52.237
I just want to find out
what's wrong

02:52.239 --> 02:53.505
With your daughter's knee.
Why don't we do this?

02:53.507 --> 02:55.174
Let's get her in
for an mri right away,

02:55.176 --> 02:57.176
Take a couple of pictures,
and just, you know,

02:57.178 --> 02:59.478
See if we can't rule out
any serious damage.

02:59.480 --> 03:02.381
Okay. You get her in,
you get her out,

03:02.383 --> 03:04.716
You take care of this,
and we're forever in your debt.

03:04.718 --> 03:06.451
Good.

03:06.453 --> 03:08.187
Okay.

03:08.189 --> 03:10.455
[ helicopter blades whirring ]

03:10.457 --> 03:13.525
You, uh, covering call
in the o.R. Again?

03:13.527 --> 03:15.794
Beats selling mattresses.

03:15.796 --> 03:18.197
Can I give you
some advice?

03:18.199 --> 03:19.932
Can I stop you?

03:19.934 --> 03:23.835
You need a niche, reid,
if you want to get ahead.

03:23.837 --> 03:25.637
[ telephone rings ]

03:25.639 --> 03:27.339
Case in point --

03:27.341 --> 03:29.241
I'm about to perform
a lap whipple.

03:29.243 --> 03:32.578
Lap whipple.
Impressive.

03:32.580 --> 03:35.847
The most difficult surgery
known to man, right?

03:35.849 --> 03:37.683
My niche.

03:37.685 --> 03:38.850
Good for you,
reycraft.

03:38.852 --> 03:40.485
Think about it.

03:40.487 --> 03:41.853
[ siren wailing ]

03:41.855 --> 03:43.488
Your niche.

03:43.490 --> 03:45.857
I'd hate to see you
get passed over for a staff job.

03:45.859 --> 03:48.493
I'd miss you.

03:48.495 --> 03:51.730
Don't look at me.
I'm just a lowly e.R. Doc.

03:51.732 --> 03:53.799
Performing
lap whipples.

03:53.801 --> 03:55.667
[ laughs ]
[ woman whimpering ]

03:55.669 --> 03:56.868
Somebody, help me!

03:56.870 --> 03:58.770
[ gasping ]
I need a stretcher!

03:58.772 --> 04:01.273
We'll take it from here,
sir.

04:01.275 --> 04:03.275
[ groans ]
penetrating neck trauma --

04:03.277 --> 04:06.511
Knife wound, zone two,
clear platysmal violation.

04:06.513 --> 04:08.647
Where's the trauma bay?
We'll take her in from here.

04:08.649 --> 04:10.882
I have my finger
on her carotid artery.

04:10.884 --> 04:12.918
If I remove it,
she'll bleed out.

04:12.920 --> 04:15.454
[ crying ]

04:16.623 --> 04:19.291
Zach: All right,
here we go, guys, on three.

04:19.293 --> 04:20.926
One, two, three.

04:20.928 --> 04:22.361
Oxygen, 100%.

04:22.363 --> 04:23.795
Get some leads on her!

04:23.797 --> 04:25.530
Yeah, we got it.
Call x-ray.

04:26.599 --> 04:28.267
She'll need
two large-bore I.V.S

04:28.269 --> 04:29.868
I know.
Start the crystalloid.

04:29.870 --> 04:31.536
Run it wide open.

04:31.538 --> 04:33.272
Get me six units,
cross-matched.
She's a.B.-Negative.

04:33.274 --> 04:35.540
I need to get control
of the wound now, doctor...?

04:35.542 --> 04:36.875
Nazir.

04:36.877 --> 04:39.344
Gently. She's my wife.
Yep.

04:41.447 --> 04:42.781
I'll just take a look
at the --

04:42.783 --> 04:43.949
Yup,
that's the carotid.

04:43.951 --> 04:45.584
Alima.

04:45.586 --> 04:47.853
[ speaking arabic ]

04:47.855 --> 04:49.388
Dr. Nazir,
is that your wife's blood?

04:49.390 --> 04:51.556
[ exhales sharply ]
no, it's mine.

04:51.558 --> 04:53.759
Okay, can I get some help
over here? This guy's been cut!

04:53.761 --> 04:55.294
Hey,
don't bother about me.

04:55.296 --> 04:56.895
I-it's minor.
Just take care of alima.

04:56.897 --> 04:58.463
Let's get her to o.R.

05:00.767 --> 05:02.734
This guy's intense.

05:06.005 --> 05:07.439
[ indistinct conversations ]

05:07.441 --> 05:09.574
[ heart monitor beeping ]
what's up?

05:09.576 --> 05:11.877
Come see.

05:11.879 --> 05:15.447
[ exhales sharply ]

05:15.449 --> 05:17.015
Oh. I waited,
but no one came.

05:17.017 --> 05:19.885
The wound's superficial,
so I thought I'd do it myself.

05:19.887 --> 05:23.522
Check out his stitch.

05:23.524 --> 05:25.791
Hey, is that
a mattress stitch?

05:25.793 --> 05:27.826
Where did you learn
how to do that?

05:27.828 --> 05:30.462
This is all my fault.

05:30.464 --> 05:32.064
Some kid
grabbed alima's purse.

05:32.066 --> 05:35.801
I tried to step in
and stop him.

05:35.803 --> 05:37.402
He pulled a knife.

05:38.771 --> 05:39.938
[ exhales sharply ]

05:39.940 --> 05:41.473
What is alima's status?

05:41.475 --> 05:43.642
I repaired her carotid artery.
She's stable.

05:43.644 --> 05:46.878
Is her, uh,
blood work and imaging back?

05:46.880 --> 05:48.380
I was just going
to check.

05:48.382 --> 05:51.616
[ groans ]
good. Let's go.

05:51.618 --> 05:53.018
[ indistinct conversations ]

05:53.020 --> 05:54.886
[ telephone ringing ]

05:54.888 --> 05:57.889
Hi, jay.
Hi, arwen.

05:57.891 --> 05:59.358
Arwen:
Haven't you heard?

05:59.360 --> 06:00.592
Everybody's calling us
"jaywen" now.

06:00.594 --> 06:02.527
Right, jaywen?
That's right, jaywen.

06:02.529 --> 06:04.396
Hey, you two
play your cards right,

06:04.398 --> 06:05.997
Everyone will be calling you
"gaggie" soon.

06:05.999 --> 06:07.966
Yikes.
Blarg.

06:07.968 --> 06:09.368
You said it.

06:09.370 --> 06:12.604
Ugh. Don't you dare.
Come on.

06:12.606 --> 06:14.373
Look.
It's beautiful.

06:14.375 --> 06:16.375
<i>You</i> are beautiful.

06:17.076 --> 06:18.844
You guys are sweet.

06:18.846 --> 06:22.013
I actually came
to listen to your chest, jay.

06:22.015 --> 06:23.915
So, arwen,
big day today.

06:23.917 --> 06:26.151
Yeah.
Are you nervous?

06:27.687 --> 06:31.656
Your lungs sound like
they're improving.

06:31.658 --> 06:33.725
I think
you got this pneumonia beat.

06:33.727 --> 06:36.528
Well, that's one down,
osteosarcoma to go.

06:36.530 --> 06:39.698
Dr. Murphy, dr. Lin,
jaywen.

06:39.700 --> 06:40.966
Arwen: Dr. Hamza.

06:40.968 --> 06:42.534
Let me guess.

06:42.536 --> 06:45.771
You've come to eeg
my posterior cranial fossa.

06:45.773 --> 06:48.407
Actually, yes,
and to c.T. Your neoplasm.

06:48.409 --> 06:50.942
Jay and I
have bets on my tumor.

06:50.944 --> 06:52.110
I say it's shrinking.

06:52.112 --> 06:53.678
And I say it's not.

06:53.680 --> 06:56.081
Well, then, prepare to lose
50 bucks, jaywen.

06:56.083 --> 06:58.517
You mean, get better,

06:58.519 --> 07:01.453
Go back to the soo,
marry a steelworker?

07:01.455 --> 07:05.657
I'd rather stay here
with you.

07:08.661 --> 07:10.829
Wait. I'm sorry. Um, can you
wait till I'm finished?

07:10.831 --> 07:13.064
I'll walk you down.
I'll walk her down. Don't worry.

07:13.066 --> 07:15.700
No, thanks.
Dead woman walking.

07:17.937 --> 07:19.504
Hey, arwen.

07:21.174 --> 07:22.974
How you feeling today?

07:22.976 --> 07:25.644
What are you doing?

07:25.646 --> 07:28.580
Asking you
how you're feeling today.

07:28.582 --> 07:31.183
No.
What are you doing?

07:31.185 --> 07:32.851
Asking you how --

07:32.853 --> 07:34.219
You just lost me.

07:34.221 --> 07:35.720
I hate you!
Oh --

07:35.722 --> 07:36.888
I hate you!

07:36.890 --> 07:39.591
I hate you!
Arwen.

07:39.593 --> 07:41.726
Calm down.
Are you okay?

07:43.729 --> 07:48.667
Okay, so,
this is the mri of your knee.

07:48.669 --> 07:51.236
That is
your cartilage there.

07:51.238 --> 07:52.604
It's fine.

07:52.606 --> 07:56.608
However,
your meniscus --

07:56.610 --> 07:58.910
It's pretty
badly damaged.

07:58.912 --> 08:00.111
What are you saying?

08:00.113 --> 08:02.214
She needs
a meniscus transplant.

08:02.216 --> 08:03.615
What? No.

08:03.617 --> 08:05.517
Hear me out, please.

08:05.519 --> 08:10.155
What I would do is secure
an allograft to the shinbone,

08:10.157 --> 08:11.990
Replacing the meniscus
completely.

08:11.992 --> 08:14.526
That should alleviate
the concentric stresses,

08:14.528 --> 08:16.194
Give you back
the shock absorption

08:16.196 --> 08:18.563
That you've lost
from years of playing.

08:18.565 --> 08:20.632
And look --
I would recommend doing this now

08:20.634 --> 08:22.167
Before
developing arthritis.

08:22.169 --> 08:23.802
Ricki's playing the french
in less than three weeks.

08:23.804 --> 08:25.203
Well,
she wouldn't be able to.

08:25.205 --> 08:27.772
Look -- this recovery,
including your physio --

08:27.774 --> 08:29.908
You're looking at
at least six months.

08:29.910 --> 08:31.276
[ laughs ]

08:31.278 --> 08:33.178
Come on.

08:33.180 --> 08:34.646
Ricki, look,
you're the one

08:34.648 --> 08:35.847
That has to deal with
this pain in your knee.

08:35.849 --> 08:37.883
Hey, if ricki has a pain
in her knee,

08:37.885 --> 08:39.518
We   <i>al</i>have a pain
in our knee.

08:39.520 --> 08:41.720
Well --
it's up to you, champ.

08:41.722 --> 08:43.989
I have to play
in the open.

08:43.991 --> 08:46.958
If you don't
have this operation soon,

08:46.960 --> 08:49.628
You might not be able
to walk in 10 years.

08:49.630 --> 08:51.730
Hey,
she's made her decision.

08:51.732 --> 08:53.565
Okay, I wish I could tell you
what you want to hear.

08:53.567 --> 08:54.900
It's just --
that's okay.

08:54.902 --> 08:57.102
Someone will.

08:57.104 --> 08:59.804
[ sighs ]

08:59.806 --> 09:01.306
Oh.

09:01.308 --> 09:03.942
For your trouble.

09:03.944 --> 09:08.146
"me and ricki: One father's
journey to tennis superstardom."

09:08.148 --> 09:10.682
You should check out
chapter five.

09:10.684 --> 09:13.218
There's an orthopedic surgeon
makes an appearance.

09:13.220 --> 09:15.153
[ chuckles ]
he's a total hack.

09:15.155 --> 09:17.923
Afternoon.

09:17.925 --> 09:19.758
Sorry if this hurts,
mr. Moodie.

09:19.760 --> 09:22.093
Oh, that's okay.
You're not gonna hurt me.

09:22.095 --> 09:24.095
¶ I feel good

09:24.097 --> 09:25.730
Well, that means
the sedative's working,

09:25.732 --> 09:27.065
And that's good.

09:27.067 --> 09:28.934
By the way,
call me kevin.

09:28.936 --> 09:33.672
Uh, yeah. Kevin,
how did you dislocate your hip?

09:33.674 --> 09:34.906
That's not
an easy thing to do.

09:34.908 --> 09:37.709
Walking our dogs.
We have 12 dogs.

09:37.711 --> 09:39.711
They're rescues.
Shasta takes off.

09:39.713 --> 09:41.012
She's still on leash,

09:41.014 --> 09:43.848
Gets caught between my legs,
flips me on my back --

09:43.850 --> 09:46.718
Boom -- I'm lying
in excruciating pain.

09:46.720 --> 09:48.587
Shasta's
in obedience training.

09:48.589 --> 09:50.722
It's not working out
so well.

09:50.724 --> 09:52.824
Okay, well,
we're going to put you under

09:52.826 --> 09:54.125
And get that hip
back in place.

09:54.127 --> 09:57.295
Now, julie, you can either
wait outside or stay here.

09:57.297 --> 09:58.964
I'll stay.

09:58.966 --> 10:01.600
Okeydokey.

10:01.602 --> 10:03.001
Push of propofol.

10:03.003 --> 10:04.836
[ heart monitor beeping ]

10:04.838 --> 10:08.607
[ indistinct speaking
over p.A. ]

10:08.609 --> 10:11.042
[ exhales sharply ]
is he out?

10:13.012 --> 10:15.614
You got it?
Yep.

10:17.883 --> 10:19.084
Nope.

10:27.793 --> 10:29.928
Put some muscle
into it.

10:32.031 --> 10:34.032
[ bones crack ]

10:34.034 --> 10:35.734
What was that?

10:35.736 --> 10:38.770
Uh...

10:38.772 --> 10:41.039
[ speaking arabic ]

10:44.644 --> 10:47.379
[ speaking arabic ]

10:47.381 --> 10:50.048
[ voice breaking ]
I'm sorry.

10:50.050 --> 10:52.384
[ speaking arabic ]

10:55.021 --> 10:57.722
[ speaking arabic ]

11:03.195 --> 11:05.130
[ clears throat ]

11:05.132 --> 11:06.898
What's worrying me

11:06.900 --> 11:08.833
Is that she doesn't
seem to be clotting.

11:08.835 --> 11:11.269
Her coags are off,
her platelets are low,

11:11.271 --> 11:14.305
And her inr is --
is 1.7.

11:14.307 --> 11:16.107
Her wound
is still oozing.

11:16.109 --> 11:18.810
Could be her liver --
portal hypertension?

11:18.812 --> 11:20.779
No, she's suffered
massive blood loss,

11:20.781 --> 11:23.715
Spent all
her clotting factors.

11:23.717 --> 11:25.450
This happens
with trauma patients.

11:25.452 --> 11:26.951
She just needs time.

11:26.953 --> 11:30.221
Dr. Nazir, there are
a couple cops in the e.R.

11:30.223 --> 11:32.991
They just want to talk to you
about the stabbing,

11:32.993 --> 11:35.960
Brought you
some clean clothes.

11:35.962 --> 11:37.295
Thank you.

11:37.297 --> 11:40.865
We'll give you
a few minutes.

11:40.867 --> 11:43.134
[ cellphone vibrating ]

11:46.439 --> 11:47.906
That's
a little unorthodox,

11:47.908 --> 11:49.374
You letting him
treat his own wife,

11:49.376 --> 11:51.076
No matter how awesome
he is.

11:51.078 --> 11:53.945
I was given a lot of leeway
when it came to charlie's care.

11:53.947 --> 11:56.147
I'm just
paying it forward.

11:56.149 --> 11:59.017
[ telephone rings ]

11:59.019 --> 12:01.720
Hi.
Hey.

12:01.722 --> 12:03.054
You paged?

12:03.056 --> 12:06.424
Yeah. Have you looked into
memory foam?

12:06.426 --> 12:09.394
You paged me
to talk beds?

12:09.396 --> 12:10.729
No.
I actually paged you

12:10.731 --> 12:11.963
To watch you
walk through the door.

12:11.965 --> 12:14.999
That never gets old.
[ monitors beeping ]

12:15.001 --> 12:18.369
What's going on
with you?

12:18.371 --> 12:21.072
Listen,
I'm sorry for, um...

12:21.074 --> 12:23.041
Zoning out
on you earlier.

12:23.043 --> 12:25.844
That was not cool.

12:25.846 --> 12:27.011
Truth?

12:27.013 --> 12:28.246
Always.

12:28.248 --> 12:29.948
[ inhales sharply ]

12:29.950 --> 12:31.516
We're not getting married
right now.

12:31.518 --> 12:33.017
We decided that.
No need, right?

12:33.019 --> 12:34.185
Right.

12:34.187 --> 12:36.821
But the bed thing --

12:36.823 --> 12:39.758
I mean [chuckles]
I know it seems ridiculous,

12:39.760 --> 12:41.259
But it's our place,
charlie.

12:41.261 --> 12:42.427
It's important to me.

12:42.429 --> 12:47.031
Okay. I got it.

12:47.033 --> 12:48.767
Okay.

12:48.769 --> 12:51.436
You mad at me?

12:51.438 --> 12:54.005
No.
Are you mad at me?

12:54.007 --> 12:55.173
No.

12:55.175 --> 12:57.876
Okay, then.

12:57.878 --> 12:59.077
Okay.

12:59.079 --> 13:00.111
Better get back.

13:00.113 --> 13:02.313
I'm gonna
watch you walk away.

13:06.919 --> 13:08.386
I have
kevin moodie's scans.

13:08.388 --> 13:09.554
Okay.

13:09.556 --> 13:11.022
What do they tell us?

13:11.024 --> 13:13.091
The bone
looks moth-eaten.

13:13.093 --> 13:14.459
Okay.
That's not enough.

13:14.461 --> 13:15.960
What about
the blood work?

13:15.962 --> 13:18.563
Hemoglobin's 45,
platelet count is 50 --

13:18.565 --> 13:20.064
Both super low --

13:20.066 --> 13:25.203
And his white blood cell count
is a sky-high 200.

13:25.205 --> 13:27.472
Okay, dr. Lin.

13:27.474 --> 13:29.507
What's our next move?

13:29.509 --> 13:32.043
[ sighs ]
we tell him.

13:32.045 --> 13:34.078
I wish this was better news,
kevin,

13:34.080 --> 13:36.347
But, um,
the blood work has confirmed

13:36.349 --> 13:37.549
That you have leukemia.

13:37.551 --> 13:39.083
Which is why
I broke your leg.

13:39.085 --> 13:41.986
Your bones and joints
are very fragile.

13:41.988 --> 13:43.454
You're gonna need
chemotherapy,

13:43.456 --> 13:45.423
Followed by
a bone-marrow transplant.

13:45.425 --> 13:49.494
Now, that's assuming that
we can find the right donor.

13:49.496 --> 13:53.164
Do you have siblings?

13:53.166 --> 13:54.165
Do you have kids?

13:54.167 --> 13:56.267
Our dogs
are our children.

13:56.269 --> 13:57.535
Okay.

13:57.537 --> 13:59.871
We'll put your name
in the registry

13:59.873 --> 14:02.106
And see if we can find
a suitable match.

14:02.108 --> 14:04.509
Um, obviously,
the key going forward

14:04.511 --> 14:06.511
Will be to learn
to stay positive.

14:06.513 --> 14:10.949
[ voice breaking ] well, he's
definitely got a lot of love.

14:10.951 --> 14:13.484
All right.
In the meantime,

14:13.486 --> 14:16.221
I'd like to get you into surgery
and repair that leg.

14:19.258 --> 14:21.192
Black?

14:21.194 --> 14:23.094
Thank you.

14:23.096 --> 14:26.397
The police have her attacker
in custody.

14:26.399 --> 14:28.366
That's good.

14:28.368 --> 14:34.239
Mm. They showed me photos,
and there he was.

14:34.241 --> 14:36.140
Well, that's a relief,
at least.

14:36.142 --> 14:41.512
A fellowship in
hepatopancreatobiliary surgery.

14:41.514 --> 14:42.881
Say that
five times fast.

14:42.883 --> 14:44.182
[ chuckles ]

14:44.184 --> 14:45.450
Is this for you?

14:45.452 --> 14:47.085
I have to find my niche.

14:47.087 --> 14:51.256
I don't understand
this mania for specialization.

14:51.258 --> 14:54.392
Help more people
with more problems?

14:54.394 --> 14:55.960
Don't you have a niche?

14:55.962 --> 14:57.295
I'm a trauma surgeon.

14:57.297 --> 14:59.564
It should be
about the patients,

14:59.566 --> 15:03.368
Not the doctor
or, uh, the gadgets.

15:03.370 --> 15:06.104
That's not
the way it is.
It should be.

15:06.106 --> 15:10.108
[ woman over p.A. ] <i>code white,</i>
<i>room 314, code white.</i>

15:10.110 --> 15:12.577
She's ripping her lines out
and freaking out.

15:12.579 --> 15:13.945
Alima, alima!

15:13.947 --> 15:15.914
[ speaking arabic ]
alima!

15:15.916 --> 15:18.049
She needs sedation.
Let us work.

15:18.051 --> 15:19.918
2 milligrams haloperidol.

15:19.920 --> 15:22.287
Move! Move!
Scratch the haloperidol.

15:22.289 --> 15:25.590
She's seizing.
2 milligrams of lorazepam.

15:25.592 --> 15:27.492
Please --
let me
take care of her!

15:27.494 --> 15:29.060
Just let him go.
Let him go.

15:29.062 --> 15:31.195
Okay. Oxygen, wide open.
Where's my lorazepam?

15:31.197 --> 15:33.564
Alima. Alima.

15:33.566 --> 15:35.199
Alima: [ groaning ]
sharp out!

15:35.201 --> 15:36.534
Give me the syringe.
Steady her shoulder.

15:36.536 --> 15:37.702
I've got this.
I'll do it!

15:37.704 --> 15:40.104
Doctor,
I've got this.

15:43.175 --> 15:44.342
Alima. Alima.

15:44.344 --> 15:46.477
[ breathing heavily ]

15:56.689 --> 15:58.189
[ heart monitor beeping ]

15:58.191 --> 15:59.590
Any evidence of
electrolyte imbalance?

15:59.592 --> 16:01.159
Alex: None.

16:01.161 --> 16:03.094
No reason to believe
she's having an adverse reaction

16:03.096 --> 16:04.696
To the medication
we've been giving her.

16:04.698 --> 16:06.698
She's not epileptic.

16:06.700 --> 16:09.567
Right, and no sign of stroke
or brain injury.

16:09.569 --> 16:11.302
C.T.S are normal?
Yeah.

16:11.304 --> 16:13.371
And the tox screen
was negative for benzos.

16:13.373 --> 16:14.672
Of course.

16:14.674 --> 16:16.274
Wait.

16:16.276 --> 16:17.608
Her alcohol levels
were through the roof.

16:17.610 --> 16:19.243
Alcohol?

16:19.245 --> 16:21.512
Yeah. When they brought her in,
your wife was drunk.

16:21.514 --> 16:22.981
Oh, that's impossible.

16:22.983 --> 16:24.515
And now the alcohol's
leaving her system.

16:24.517 --> 16:26.050
Delirium tremens?

16:26.052 --> 16:28.119
Seizures, aggression.
It fits with the d.T.S.

16:28.121 --> 16:30.388
My wife doesn't drink.
This is absurd.

16:30.390 --> 16:33.024
If she has cirrhosis
from alcoholism,

16:33.026 --> 16:34.625
That would explain
why she's not clotting.

16:34.627 --> 16:37.128
[ coughs ]
she's spitting up blood.

16:37.130 --> 16:39.263
We need
to move forward fast.

16:39.265 --> 16:41.366
We have to find
the source of the bleeding.

16:41.368 --> 16:42.700
Let's get her
into endoscopy.

16:42.702 --> 16:44.102
I'll book a room
for you.

16:44.104 --> 16:45.403
Okay, let's turn her.

16:45.405 --> 16:46.671
One, two, three.

16:46.673 --> 16:48.039
[ gasps ]

16:48.041 --> 16:49.474
Dr. Reid,
I'd like to go with you.

16:49.476 --> 16:50.641
Of course.

16:50.643 --> 16:52.677
We're a team now.

16:52.679 --> 16:55.013
[ telephone rings ]

16:55.015 --> 16:56.647
Hey.
Come on in, man.

16:56.649 --> 16:59.350
I'm hearing rumors
that ricki wilkens
is floating around.

16:59.352 --> 17:00.718
What can I do for you,
charlie?

17:00.720 --> 17:02.186
I reshuffled
my o.R. Block.

17:02.188 --> 17:03.554
I need you
to sign off on it.

17:03.556 --> 17:06.557
"ricki and me," huh?
You doing her surgery?

17:06.559 --> 17:08.159
Nope.

17:08.161 --> 17:10.628
That's a badly damaged
lateral meniscus.

17:10.630 --> 17:12.363
Would you do a transplant
on that knee?

17:12.365 --> 17:13.698
Oh, hell, yeah.
It's the only way.

17:13.700 --> 17:15.299
Recovery's a bitch,
though.

17:15.301 --> 17:18.369
Yeah. It's not the news
that superdad wanted to hear,

17:18.371 --> 17:20.538
So he is taking the famous knee
elsewhere.

17:20.540 --> 17:22.173
That's too bad.
It would have brought

17:22.175 --> 17:23.674
Some profitable attention
to the hospital.

17:23.676 --> 17:25.143
Well, she didn't want
the surgery,

17:25.145 --> 17:28.179
So I had to let her walk.
That happens.

17:28.181 --> 17:30.314
You would've done
the same thing?

17:30.316 --> 17:32.450
No.

17:32.452 --> 17:36.788
I would have made her
want what I want.

17:38.457 --> 17:41.159
The glioma didn't react to
the chemotherapy as we'd hoped.

17:41.161 --> 17:43.227
The tumor remains
4 1/2 centimeters

17:43.229 --> 17:46.297
And is still
impinging on the brain stem.

17:46.299 --> 17:48.466
So,
it's inoperable.

17:48.468 --> 17:50.334
And she knows?

17:50.336 --> 17:52.403
I think
she was expecting bad news.

17:52.405 --> 17:54.272
That explains
why she was so angry earlier.

17:54.274 --> 17:55.606
She was
probably terrified.

17:55.608 --> 17:57.141
Now,
these types of tumors

17:57.143 --> 17:59.544
Often precipitate
radical swings in emotion.

17:59.546 --> 18:03.681
Either way.

18:03.683 --> 18:05.216
[ sighs ]

18:05.218 --> 18:07.485
So, can we begin our session
with you telling me

18:07.487 --> 18:12.490
About hope and silver linings
and glittery unicorns?

18:12.492 --> 18:16.627
I'm sorry that the chemo
didn't shrink the tumor.

18:16.629 --> 18:19.497
Whatever.

18:19.499 --> 18:21.766
Six months, all my hair.

18:21.768 --> 18:24.402
But, hey,
I won 50 bucks.

18:24.404 --> 18:26.337
Silver lining.

18:26.339 --> 18:29.240
Now I want to hear about
the glittery unicorns.

18:29.242 --> 18:30.241
Okay.

18:30.243 --> 18:32.743
Well,
what is a unicorn?

18:32.745 --> 18:34.112
Let's start there.

18:34.114 --> 18:37.448
A horse freak.

18:37.450 --> 18:40.118
Because of the horn?

18:40.120 --> 18:42.854
Yeah.
Horses don't have horns.

18:42.856 --> 18:46.424
I know.
I used to ride them.

18:46.426 --> 18:51.529
Do you feel
like you're a freak?

18:51.531 --> 18:54.799
May as well be.

18:54.801 --> 18:56.534
[ voice breaking ] I'm 16

18:56.536 --> 18:59.837
And I have this stupid tumor
the size of a plum

18:59.839 --> 19:05.710
And it's gonna kill me,
like, soon.

19:05.712 --> 19:10.181
And I broke up
with my boyfriend.

19:10.183 --> 19:13.284
Yeah,
maybe let's talk about that.

19:13.286 --> 19:17.421
Why did you break up
with jay?

19:17.423 --> 19:21.559
Okay, no infection.
Looks good.

19:21.561 --> 19:25.830
Hey, dr. Lin, have you heard
anything about arwen?

19:25.832 --> 19:27.665
I'm sorry.

19:27.667 --> 19:30.268
I can't discuss a patient's care
with someone who isn't family.

19:30.270 --> 19:33.871
Got to be family, huh?

19:33.873 --> 19:35.439
Why don't you
ask her yourself?

19:35.441 --> 19:37.208
She's not gonna
talk to me again.

19:37.210 --> 19:38.910
Why is that?

19:38.912 --> 19:43.314
[ sighs ]
it was a deal-breaker.

19:43.316 --> 19:45.416
See, we have these things,
these deal-breakers,

19:45.418 --> 19:47.251
And I knew that was hers.

19:47.253 --> 19:48.619
And we made this pact.

19:48.621 --> 19:50.655
I wasn't supposed to ask her
how she was feeling.

19:50.657 --> 19:51.822
So, why did you, then?

19:51.824 --> 19:54.392
I don't know.

19:58.564 --> 20:01.599
Maybe you wanted her
to break up with you?

20:01.601 --> 20:05.336
I don't know.

20:05.338 --> 20:07.538
What's your deal-breaker?

20:07.540 --> 20:13.611
Well,
I've got doctors poking

20:13.613 --> 20:16.447
And, you know,
pushing at me all day, so...

20:16.449 --> 20:17.515
[ chuckles ]

20:17.517 --> 20:18.950
I'm like
their personal pincushion.

20:18.952 --> 20:20.318
No offense.

20:20.320 --> 20:22.286
So, I don't know.

20:22.288 --> 20:24.222
I don't --
I don't like being touched.

20:24.224 --> 20:26.490
[ breathes deeply ]

20:26.492 --> 20:28.859
So,
arwen never touches you?

20:28.861 --> 20:32.630
No.

20:32.632 --> 20:37.368
That's my thing.

20:37.370 --> 20:41.239
Gail, no.
No, I'm -- I'm gonna be okay.

20:41.241 --> 20:42.907
Just stay put.

20:42.909 --> 20:45.810
No.
Don't pack everyone up.

20:45.812 --> 20:46.978
Okay, sir --
phone, please.

20:46.980 --> 20:49.247
Gail,
I'm gonna be fine.

20:49.249 --> 20:50.514
Just please don't cry.
Victor?

20:50.516 --> 20:51.983
Please don't cry.
I'm sorry, sir.

20:51.985 --> 20:53.384
It's time
to say goodbye.

20:53.386 --> 20:54.986
I got to go, honey.
Bye. I love you.

20:54.988 --> 20:56.520
Children:
Bye! We love you!

20:56.522 --> 20:57.989
[ sighs ]

20:57.991 --> 20:59.757
I thought
you didn't have kids?

20:59.759 --> 21:01.525
Oh, I-I-I don't.

21:01.527 --> 21:04.729
That's, uh --
they're julia's sister's.

21:04.731 --> 21:06.664
[ monitors beeping ]

21:06.666 --> 21:11.269
Okay, we've achieved
good fixation.

21:11.271 --> 21:12.903
[ exhales sharply ]

21:12.905 --> 21:14.739
Bone-cement gun.

21:14.741 --> 21:16.641
We don't have a lot of time.
The cement's starting to set.

21:16.643 --> 21:18.809
Yep. We'll fill in the defect,
and then we'll close.

21:18.811 --> 21:21.545
[ gun clicking ]

21:21.547 --> 21:22.780
[ monitor beeping erratically ]

21:22.782 --> 21:25.416
What did you do?
His sats are dropping.

21:25.418 --> 21:26.751
Cement must have
pressurized the canal.

21:26.753 --> 21:28.286
Could be a fat embolism.

21:28.288 --> 21:29.520
I don't know,
but he's going into v-fib.

21:29.522 --> 21:30.955
Call in the code.
Get him closed up.

21:30.957 --> 21:32.623
We need to shock him.
Get the pads on him.

21:32.625 --> 21:35.293
[ woman over p.A. ]
<i>code blue, o.R. 1.</i>

21:35.295 --> 21:37.795
<i>Code blue, o.R. 1.</i>

21:37.797 --> 21:40.765
<i>Code blue, o.R. 1.</i>

21:40.767 --> 21:43.534
<i>What...</i>

21:43.536 --> 21:44.702
Oh, crap.

21:44.704 --> 21:45.870
<i>What the hell?</i>

21:45.872 --> 21:47.305
That's not good.

21:47.307 --> 21:50.574
Dr. Harris,
are we closing?

21:50.576 --> 21:52.610
Yeah.
[ defibrillator humming ]

21:52.612 --> 21:55.346
Clear.

21:59.451 --> 22:01.385
[ monitor emits tone ]

22:05.424 --> 22:07.591
Using a six-shooter
sucks the varices in,

22:07.593 --> 22:10.494
Wraps an elastic around them,
stops the bleeding.

22:12.731 --> 22:14.031
[ air hissing ]

22:14.033 --> 22:15.800
Hmm.
Doesn't seem to be stopping.

22:15.802 --> 22:16.967
There's a lot of blood.

22:16.969 --> 22:18.336
Yeah.

22:18.338 --> 22:19.904
We may need
to try something else.

22:19.906 --> 22:21.472
What are you thinking?

22:21.474 --> 22:22.707
Another, uh, gadget?

22:22.709 --> 22:25.409
A better gadget --
called t.I.P.S.

22:25.411 --> 22:26.877
We don't have time
for t.I.P.S.

22:26.879 --> 22:28.346
Her liver isn't working.

22:28.348 --> 22:30.014
We need to open her up,
do a warren shunt.

22:30.016 --> 22:31.615
A warren shunt?

22:31.617 --> 22:32.950
That's one of the most
invasive surgeries there is.

22:32.952 --> 22:34.719
And an incision that big?

22:34.721 --> 22:37.355
She's lost too much blood.
She won't survive a big surgery.

22:37.357 --> 22:40.358
All due respect,
before coming here, in syria,

22:40.360 --> 22:44.428
I was performing surgery
in a cave, under fire.

22:44.430 --> 22:46.430
You want a niche?
Blood is my niche.

22:46.432 --> 22:48.399
So, trust me.
Do the warren shunt.

22:48.401 --> 22:49.834
You need
to trust <i>me</i> here.

22:49.836 --> 22:51.802
If we don't do this,
she's not going to survive.

22:54.773 --> 22:56.640
Okay.

22:56.642 --> 22:58.943
<i>If</i> we did
a warren shunt --

22:58.945 --> 23:00.745
[ knock on door ]

23:00.747 --> 23:03.614
Reid, can you just step outside
here for a minute, please?

23:03.616 --> 23:05.783
[ indistinct speaking
over p.A. ]

23:09.756 --> 23:12.857
There was an airport limo
double-parked earlier,

23:12.859 --> 23:15.426
Blocking
the ambulance bay.
Okay.

23:15.428 --> 23:17.395
So, they find blood
on the seat.

23:17.397 --> 23:20.598
I guess
he was driving with one hand,

23:20.600 --> 23:22.600
Compressing her neck
with the other.

23:22.602 --> 23:25.536
It's unbelievable.

23:25.538 --> 23:27.905
He's not a doctor.

23:27.907 --> 23:29.607
He's a limo driver.

23:34.746 --> 23:37.715
You lied to me.
You're not a doctor.

23:37.717 --> 23:39.517
Of course I'm a doctor.
Really?

23:39.519 --> 23:40.718
Airport limo
says otherwise.

23:40.720 --> 23:42.753
Dr. Reid --
you treated a patient.

23:42.755 --> 23:44.789
You put all of us --
this hospital, me --

23:44.791 --> 23:46.090
In serious jeopardy.

23:46.092 --> 23:47.658
Just because
this country

23:47.660 --> 23:48.959
Doesn't accept
my accreditation doesn't mean --

23:48.961 --> 23:51.529
You tried to talk me into
doing a massive surgery!

23:51.531 --> 23:52.763
Do you even understand
the liability?

23:52.765 --> 23:55.533
Liability?!
She's my wife!

23:55.535 --> 23:56.867
And if she wasn't
your wife,

23:56.869 --> 23:59.437
I would kick you out on your ass
right now!

23:59.439 --> 24:02.840
Prep her for t.I.P.S.

24:02.842 --> 24:04.675
[ door opens ]

24:08.513 --> 24:10.047
Why won't you
listen to me?

24:10.049 --> 24:11.549
I  <i>did</i>listen.

24:11.551 --> 24:13.484
Oh, right,
now that I'm just a chauffeur.

24:13.486 --> 24:15.186
This is my decision
as her doctor.

24:15.188 --> 24:18.189
Please. I brought her here
to save her life.

24:18.191 --> 24:19.990
Take mrs. Nazir
to o.R. 2.

24:19.992 --> 24:21.158
I'll be right there.

24:21.160 --> 24:24.728
You...

24:24.730 --> 24:28.933
You can watch
from the gallery.

24:28.935 --> 24:31.068
[ heart monitor beeping ]

24:31.070 --> 24:34.004
<i>Uh,</i>
<i>how long till I wake up?</i>

24:35.941 --> 24:38.609
Don't know, kev,
but a fat embolism

24:38.611 --> 24:40.878
Is a lot less serious
than a blood clot, so...

24:40.880 --> 24:44.682
Well, that machine over there
is breathing for you,

24:44.684 --> 24:46.116
But the embolism
will pass.

24:46.118 --> 24:48.686
You will wake up.
<i>When?</i>

24:48.688 --> 24:51.989
<i>You see, it's really important</i>
<i>that I wake up now.</i>

24:51.991 --> 24:55.125
<i>Oh, no.</i>

24:55.127 --> 24:57.761
<i>This isn't happening.</i>

24:57.763 --> 24:58.963
What?

25:00.665 --> 25:04.168
<i>Okay, here's what</i>
<i>you're gonna do.</i>

25:04.170 --> 25:06.036
<i>Julia's home</i>
<i>getting clothes.</i>

25:06.038 --> 25:07.738
<i>When she comes back,</i>
<i>if you head her off,</i>

25:07.740 --> 25:09.206
<i>Then she won't see</i>
<i>gail and the girls.</i>

25:09.208 --> 25:11.842
Gail is...

25:13.979 --> 25:15.513
<i>My wife.</i>

25:17.115 --> 25:18.916
<i>My</i> other <i>wife.</i>

25:21.620 --> 25:23.787
You've got two wives?

25:23.789 --> 25:24.989
<i>Yeah.</i>

25:24.991 --> 25:26.156
[  <i>chuckles nervously</i>]

25:26.158 --> 25:28.526
<i>Those are my girls --</i>

25:28.528 --> 25:31.762
<i>Kelly and sassy.</i>

25:31.764 --> 25:35.866
So, your wife julia
doesn't know about the --

25:35.868 --> 25:37.968
<i>No, none of it.</i>

25:40.238 --> 25:42.039
Well, this is
quite a situation, kevin.

25:42.041 --> 25:46.076
<i>I-I met gail,</i>
<i>and, well, we started a family.</i>

25:46.078 --> 25:48.812
<i>And I was really happy</i>
<i>and then, uh...</i>

25:48.814 --> 25:53.117
<i>Well, I met julia</i>
<i>and I was really happy, too.</i>

25:53.119 --> 25:55.686
<i>I don't know.</i>
<i>It just kind of happened.</i>
<i>[ chuckles ]</i>

25:55.688 --> 26:01.325
Okay, well, bigamy aside,
um, you're sick.

26:01.327 --> 26:02.960
And you need
a bone-marrow transplant

26:02.962 --> 26:04.995
If you're gonna have a real shot
of surviving this.

26:04.997 --> 26:07.898
And the best shot you're gonna
have of finding a match

26:07.900 --> 26:10.000
Is gonna be
with one of your daughters.

26:10.002 --> 26:12.336
So, I'm thinking...

26:12.338 --> 26:14.872
Maybe time to come clean
with all of this.

26:22.847 --> 26:24.715
So...

26:24.717 --> 26:28.285
A chauffeur
posing as a surgeon.

26:28.287 --> 26:29.920
What is this,
"the bourne identity"?

26:29.922 --> 26:31.956
Am I in trouble?
No, of course not.

26:31.958 --> 26:33.791
Come on.
He snowed everyone.

26:35.860 --> 26:38.596
The thing is, is he kind of
inspired me, you know?

26:38.598 --> 26:40.364
And it felt good.

26:40.366 --> 26:42.633
I guess
I'm just disappointed.

26:42.635 --> 26:46.303
[ pager beeps, vibrates ]
so, stay inspired.

26:46.305 --> 26:48.072
Looks good on you.

26:52.778 --> 26:57.715
My father talked
to other orthopods.

26:57.717 --> 27:02.953
All of them said I'd be able
to play without the surgery.

27:02.955 --> 27:04.388
Okay.

27:04.390 --> 27:07.358
I think they're wrong,
but glad that you guys

27:07.360 --> 27:08.892
Have found someone
you think you can work with.

27:08.894 --> 27:10.661
Well,
that's the thing.

27:10.663 --> 27:13.063
You're the only surgeon
who looked me in the eye

27:13.065 --> 27:17.301
And talked to <i>me --</i>
<i>not my father, not my coach --</i>

27:17.303 --> 27:18.869
Me.

27:21.006 --> 27:23.073
Does your father know
that you're here?

27:23.075 --> 27:25.275
[ chuckles ]
thinks I'm getting a bikini wax.

27:25.277 --> 27:29.179
Look, I know how much pain
your knee must be in right now.

27:29.181 --> 27:30.914
"suck it up."

27:30.916 --> 27:35.319
That's what I've been told
my whole life.

27:35.321 --> 27:37.154
Look,
he's not a monster.

27:37.156 --> 27:41.058
I'm not saying that he is,
but, ricki, you know,

27:41.060 --> 27:43.927
Overbearing fathers
are kind of a dime a dozen.

27:43.929 --> 27:45.396
[ sighs ]

27:45.398 --> 27:48.832
Tennis is all I know.

27:48.834 --> 27:50.200
Well,
knees are kind of my thing,

27:50.202 --> 27:52.803
And I am telling you right now
you need that surgery.

27:52.805 --> 27:57.708
Well, an average bikini wax
lasts about 10 minutes.

27:57.710 --> 28:01.345
So...Convince me.

28:01.347 --> 28:03.380
All set?
All set.

28:03.382 --> 28:05.883
Dr. Reid,
can you take a look at this?

28:05.885 --> 28:07.051
Yeah.

28:07.053 --> 28:09.353
[ monitor beeping ]

28:09.355 --> 28:12.690
[ sighs ]
this is not good.

28:12.692 --> 28:14.091
Dr. Ray:
Not good, no.

28:14.093 --> 28:15.325
She's hypotensive.

28:15.327 --> 28:16.860
And she's not
making urine.

28:16.862 --> 28:18.696
Doesn't matter
how much blood we give her.

28:18.698 --> 28:20.731
Victor: Let's move, then.
Uh, guide wire?

28:22.701 --> 28:25.235
No. No guide wire.
Get rid of the fluoroscope.

28:26.705 --> 28:29.740
Let's go.
Change of plans.

28:29.742 --> 28:31.275
I'm going to be doing
a warren shunt.

28:31.277 --> 28:34.945
Get me a major vascular tray
and a thompson retractor.

28:34.947 --> 28:36.947
And page reycraft.
We're gonna need hands.

28:36.949 --> 28:40.084
This incision's gonna be
big and wide.

28:40.086 --> 28:43.721
[ woman over p.A. ]
<i>dr. Reycraft, o.R. 2, stat.</i>

28:43.723 --> 28:46.457
<i>Dr. Reycraft, o.R. 2, stat.</i>

28:51.362 --> 28:53.230
I've mobilized
the retroperitoneum.

28:53.232 --> 28:55.999
I'll tie off the veins draining
the stomach and pancreas.

28:56.001 --> 28:57.868
She's still
bleeding a lot.

28:57.870 --> 28:59.870
Then let's motor.
Pick-ups?

29:06.745 --> 29:08.779
Have you isolated the splenic
and portal vein?

29:08.781 --> 29:10.114
Pretty sure.

29:10.116 --> 29:11.882
It's impossible to see
with all this blood.

29:11.884 --> 29:13.884
I can't even see
the left renal vein.

29:13.886 --> 29:15.919
Well, we need
to anastomose the splenic

29:15.921 --> 29:18.155
To the left renal vein,
so let's find it.

29:18.157 --> 29:20.224
Gemini.

29:20.226 --> 29:21.391
[ heart monitor beeping ]

29:21.393 --> 29:22.960
Gemini.

29:22.962 --> 29:24.328
Dr. Ray: Her heart rate's up.
Pressure dropping.

29:24.330 --> 29:26.296
I'm trying to find it,
but I just can't --

29:26.298 --> 29:28.999
I'm not gonna be able to handle
the blood loss at this rate.

29:29.001 --> 29:31.502
Whatever you're doing,
do it quick, before she crashes.

29:32.904 --> 29:35.973
Reycraft, can you see it?
No. It's a bloodbath.

29:35.975 --> 29:37.541
Damn it.

29:40.178 --> 29:43.013
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
Are you out of your mind?

29:43.015 --> 29:45.048
Do you want her to die?
Because I don't.

29:45.050 --> 29:48.252
Lady, you are steely,
and I like it.

29:48.254 --> 29:50.888
Still nothing, huh?
No, I can't see anything.

29:50.890 --> 29:52.156
You can't find the renal vein,
can you?

29:52.158 --> 29:53.924
Nope,
but you're gonna help us.

29:53.926 --> 29:55.793
Talk me through
the warren shunt.

29:55.795 --> 29:58.295
I'm with you.

29:58.297 --> 29:59.463
Thank you.

29:59.465 --> 30:01.431
[ indistinct conversations ]

30:01.433 --> 30:02.833
[ strings tuning ]

30:02.835 --> 30:04.802
What's going on today?
Flash mob?

30:04.804 --> 30:08.105
It's a special day
at hope zion.

30:08.107 --> 30:10.374
Okay. Where are you taking me,
exactly?

30:10.376 --> 30:12.142
Seat, monsieur?

30:12.144 --> 30:15.078
[ chuckles ]
um, n-no, thank you.

30:15.080 --> 30:17.214
Oh, come on, jay.
Humor me.

30:17.216 --> 30:19.483
Come on.

30:19.485 --> 30:21.952
There you go.

30:21.954 --> 30:25.522
You did this?
Yeah.

30:25.524 --> 30:28.192
Oh, sorry.
Actually, I don't -- okay.

30:28.194 --> 30:30.227
Dr. Murphy, no.

30:30.229 --> 30:31.829
No, no, no,
no, no, no.
No. I am serious.

30:31.831 --> 30:33.363
I am gonna
tip this wheelchair over

30:33.365 --> 30:35.399
If you don't take me out.
No. Bring me back to the room.

30:35.401 --> 30:37.367
Maggie: It's gonna be fine.
Arwen, just give him one minute.
One.

30:37.369 --> 30:40.337
You're fired,
and I want a new shrink.

30:40.339 --> 30:42.105
So, this was your idea?

30:42.107 --> 30:44.274
No. No, no, no. No, this --
this is -- this is them.

30:45.476 --> 30:47.211
Enjoy.

30:47.213 --> 30:50.881
[ carly rae jepsen's
"call me maybe" plays ]

30:56.254 --> 30:57.421
Nice table.

30:57.423 --> 30:58.622
Nice string quartet.

30:58.624 --> 31:00.190
I think
this is gonna go well.

31:00.192 --> 31:01.358
[ sighs ]

31:05.864 --> 31:10.100
Could go either way.
Yeah.

31:10.102 --> 31:13.470
[ "call me maybe" continues ]

31:13.472 --> 31:15.405
[ monitors beeping ]

31:17.475 --> 31:19.343
Enjoy.

31:19.345 --> 31:21.912
Joel: Excuse me.

31:21.914 --> 31:23.614
What do you think
you're doing here?

31:23.616 --> 31:26.016
I'm observing the surgery,
of course.

31:26.018 --> 31:27.517
I don't think so, no.

31:27.519 --> 31:29.186
I filled out
all the requisite forms,

31:29.188 --> 31:30.220
So, yes, I am.

31:30.222 --> 31:32.155
I don't
perform to a crowd.

31:32.157 --> 31:34.458
I can't believe you went
behind my back for all this.

31:34.460 --> 31:35.626
Hey.

31:35.628 --> 31:37.027
You can save your chat
for later.

31:37.029 --> 31:38.662
Look,
I just want to make sure

31:38.664 --> 31:40.330
That my little knee
gets through this okay.

31:40.332 --> 31:42.299
Look, it's not really
your little knee, is it, mate?

31:42.301 --> 31:43.634
[ chuckles ]
it's ricki's little knee.

31:43.636 --> 31:45.035
It's never
just about ricki.

31:45.037 --> 31:46.570
Actually,
right now it is.

31:46.572 --> 31:48.639
What you don't understand
is that she is an industry.

31:48.641 --> 31:52.175
What she is,
is in pain,

31:52.177 --> 31:54.444
A lot more pain than
she's been telling you about.

31:54.446 --> 31:57.047
I'm about to fix that.

31:57.049 --> 31:58.181
Okay.

31:58.183 --> 32:01.184
Okay.

32:01.186 --> 32:03.186
I'm just gonna stand
right over here --

32:03.188 --> 32:06.690
Get the hell
out of my o.R.

32:17.468 --> 32:20.237
If I knew it was that easy
to tell off my dad...

32:20.239 --> 32:21.672
Actually,
it wasn't that easy,

32:21.674 --> 32:24.474
But I'll tell you...

32:24.476 --> 32:27.210
Strangely satisfying.

32:27.212 --> 32:29.346
[ sighs ]

32:29.348 --> 32:30.948
Hi, kevin.

32:30.950 --> 32:32.482
[ groans ]

32:32.484 --> 32:35.085
Dr. Harris.

32:35.087 --> 32:36.954
What happened?
Am I okay?

32:36.956 --> 32:39.456
Um, you suffered
what's called a fat embolism

32:39.458 --> 32:41.091
During your surgery.

32:41.093 --> 32:44.328
You've been unconscious
for a couple hours.

32:44.330 --> 32:47.631
What's the last thing
you remember?

32:47.633 --> 32:51.702
[ sighs ]
I was on the phone.

32:51.704 --> 32:53.470
And nothing after that?

32:53.472 --> 32:55.005
No. No.

32:55.007 --> 32:56.606
I woke up,
and here we are.

32:56.608 --> 32:58.542
[ chuckles ]
okay.

32:58.544 --> 33:05.215
Well, um, it's time
to talk to your wives, kevin.

33:05.217 --> 33:07.417
One of your daughters
could be a bone-marrow match,

33:07.419 --> 33:10.087
And we can start your treatments
right away.

33:10.089 --> 33:12.122
Daughters? Sorry.

33:12.124 --> 33:14.658
I know your secret,
kevin.

33:14.660 --> 33:16.526
There are
two women out there

33:16.528 --> 33:20.697
And two adorable little girls
who call you daddy.

33:20.699 --> 33:24.401
They all want you
to live.

33:24.403 --> 33:25.602
How did you --

33:25.604 --> 33:30.007
I just --
I know, okay?

33:30.009 --> 33:32.743
Now, either you tell them,
or I will.

33:36.280 --> 33:38.081
Your secrets
are your business, kevin,

33:38.083 --> 33:39.549
But keeping you alive
is mine.

33:39.551 --> 33:41.485
[ monitors beeping ]

33:44.655 --> 33:47.090
I'm not ready.

33:47.092 --> 33:49.159
Well,
you better get ready

33:49.161 --> 33:53.163
'cause it's
truth-telling time.

33:53.165 --> 33:55.365
[ monitors beeping ]

33:55.367 --> 33:58.668
Okay.

33:58.670 --> 34:01.571
Okay,
finished dissecting.

34:01.573 --> 34:03.507
You're going to
suture the shunt now.

34:03.509 --> 34:05.075
How's your suturing?

34:05.077 --> 34:06.777
Excellent when I can see
what I'm doing.

34:06.779 --> 34:08.311
7-0 double-armed prolene.

34:08.313 --> 34:11.081
Okay. Run the back wall
of the anast first,

34:11.083 --> 34:12.682
Toe to heel,
outside in on the renal vein.

34:12.684 --> 34:14.217
You can leave no room
for error.

34:14.219 --> 34:17.087
And you won't be able
to open her back up

34:17.089 --> 34:18.255
After all the blood
she's lost.

34:18.257 --> 34:20.424
I know.
I need quiet.

34:20.426 --> 34:22.159
[ monitors beeping ]

34:46.551 --> 34:50.287
[ beeping continues ]

34:51.722 --> 34:54.458
Let's unclamp.
Wait.

34:54.460 --> 34:56.493
Wait for what?
There's no time
to wait.

34:56.495 --> 34:59.362
Sometimes you need to go slow
to go fast.

34:59.364 --> 35:00.764
But we need to unclamp
to get the blood flow back.

35:00.766 --> 35:02.265
Slowly.

35:02.267 --> 35:04.401
You need to pinch the vein
so the redirection of flow

35:04.403 --> 35:06.770
Does not overwhelm
the anastomosis.

35:06.772 --> 35:09.106
Okay.

35:09.108 --> 35:10.574
Pinch the vein.

35:12.643 --> 35:14.244
Now what?

35:14.246 --> 35:16.179
You've created
a delicate connection.

35:16.181 --> 35:18.648
You don't want
to tear that connection apart.

35:18.650 --> 35:20.784
No. I really don't.

35:20.786 --> 35:24.221
Now let go carefully.

35:28.126 --> 35:30.760
Let's unclamp.

35:30.762 --> 35:32.863
[ monitors beeping ]

35:36.134 --> 35:37.634
Letting go.

35:42.140 --> 35:43.540
We've got flow back.

35:43.542 --> 35:44.541
Are you sure?

35:44.543 --> 35:46.743
I'm -- I'm sure.
Any leaks?

35:46.745 --> 35:48.178
No.
No, it looks good.

35:48.180 --> 35:49.679
Dr. Ray: Her heart rate's
coming down.

35:49.681 --> 35:50.847
Pressure improving.

35:50.849 --> 35:53.617
You did it.
[ exhales deeply ]

35:56.921 --> 35:58.288
[ sighs ]

35:58.290 --> 36:00.557
[ indistinct speaking over p.A ]

36:00.559 --> 36:03.393
I bet there are only
a handful of surgeons

36:03.395 --> 36:05.695
In this entire country who could
have done what you just did.

36:05.697 --> 36:06.830
[ sighs ]

36:06.832 --> 36:09.299
Well,
you're a great teacher...

36:09.301 --> 36:11.535
And a hell of doctor.
[ chuckles ]

36:11.537 --> 36:13.470
"was."

36:13.472 --> 36:16.606
[ sighs ]

36:16.608 --> 36:19.509
Our son died.

36:19.511 --> 36:22.812
I was working
in a field hospital.

36:22.814 --> 36:24.314
Alima couldn't
get to me.

36:24.316 --> 36:30.253
She had to live with that alone
for days.

36:30.255 --> 36:34.691
When she finally did
get to me...

36:34.693 --> 36:36.359
I just kept working.

36:38.896 --> 36:42.799
Then the government
started killing doctors

36:42.801 --> 36:47.604
And their families,
so we ran.

36:47.606 --> 36:49.606
[ sighs ]

36:49.608 --> 36:52.576
I should have seen the signs
with alima.

36:52.578 --> 36:55.445
I-I am a doctor.
I-I should have helped her.

36:55.447 --> 36:58.515
Being a doctor
has nothing to do with it.

37:00.851 --> 37:03.753
You're right.

37:03.755 --> 37:08.291
I need to stop
being her doctor.

37:10.861 --> 37:13.230
Now she needs a husband.

37:14.966 --> 37:18.268
You don't need to do this
to yourself.

37:18.270 --> 37:20.337
I'm okay.

37:22.506 --> 37:23.840
[ voice breaking ]
no, really, really.

37:23.842 --> 37:27.010
I'm okay.

37:30.948 --> 37:32.716
[ heart monitor beeping ]

37:36.254 --> 37:37.554
Do you feel that?

37:37.556 --> 37:38.555
Yep.

37:38.557 --> 37:40.390
Okay.
Nerves are reacting well.

37:40.392 --> 37:43.727
Pulse is very strong.

37:43.729 --> 37:45.295
It's good.

37:45.297 --> 37:48.398
I've never taken six months off
in my life,

37:48.400 --> 37:50.433
Not since I was 6.
[ chuckles ]

37:50.435 --> 37:51.801
Well, that could be
a blessing in disguise.

37:51.803 --> 37:52.969
You bet it is.

37:52.971 --> 37:54.871
Once I'm up
and moving again,

37:54.873 --> 37:56.539
I'm gonna
go on a huge trip.

37:56.541 --> 37:57.674
[ chuckles ]

37:57.676 --> 37:59.376
I've been
to hundreds of countries,

37:59.378 --> 38:02.279
But I've only seen
their tennis facilities.

38:02.281 --> 38:05.282
Is your father
gonna come with you?

38:07.018 --> 38:09.319
He's not talking to me.

38:09.321 --> 38:12.489
But that's a good thing...
For now.

38:12.491 --> 38:15.458
Okay.

38:15.460 --> 38:17.927
Hey, uh, dr. Goran,
can you pass my bag?

38:17.929 --> 38:19.496
Sure.

38:22.566 --> 38:26.036
Pick a number
between 1 and 10.

38:26.038 --> 38:27.437
Pick a number for --

38:27.439 --> 38:29.973
Just any number
between 1 and 10.

38:29.975 --> 38:31.908
3.

38:31.910 --> 38:34.711
Okay. 3.

38:34.713 --> 38:38.415
[ indistinct speaking
over p.A. ]

38:41.986 --> 38:43.553
For the hospital.

38:43.555 --> 38:46.723
I probably should have said
a higher number.

38:46.725 --> 38:50.093
[ chuckles ]
slap my name on something.

38:50.095 --> 38:52.329
A wing.

38:52.331 --> 38:54.731
[ telephone ringing ]

38:54.733 --> 38:56.066
Jay?

38:58.369 --> 39:01.338
Oh,
she didn't forgive you?

39:01.340 --> 39:03.540
[ chuckles ]

39:03.542 --> 39:04.908
Psych.

39:04.910 --> 39:06.109
It's hers.

39:06.111 --> 39:07.777
Wow, dude,
she put a ring on it.

39:07.779 --> 39:10.747
So, you're back together?
We're gonna get married.

39:10.749 --> 39:13.750
Well, when our parents
sign the releases.

39:13.752 --> 39:15.352
We're gonna be family.

39:15.354 --> 39:17.721
I'm just really very pleased
for you both.

39:17.723 --> 39:19.456
[ sighs ]

39:22.360 --> 39:24.894
Why waste time, right?

39:24.896 --> 39:27.364
Definitely.

39:27.366 --> 39:29.899
Joel.
Alex.

39:29.901 --> 39:31.368
Hey.
Hey.

39:31.370 --> 39:33.436
Trauma.
What are you
talking about?

39:33.438 --> 39:35.905
Well, that's gonna be my niche,
if you can set it up.

39:35.907 --> 39:37.374
Okay. Trauma.

39:37.376 --> 39:38.641
No. There's better choices
you can make

39:38.643 --> 39:40.009
If you want
to get noticed.

39:40.011 --> 39:42.112
I-I don't care about
being noticed anymore, okay?

39:42.114 --> 39:43.613
I just --
I want to do it all.

39:43.615 --> 39:45.382
So, trauma team leader
position?

39:45.384 --> 39:47.384
Okay, well,
I'll see what I can do.

39:47.386 --> 39:48.551
See what you can do?
Mm-hmm.

39:48.553 --> 39:49.886
You're the chief.

39:49.888 --> 39:52.389
Yeah, I guess I am the chief,
aren't I?

39:52.391 --> 39:54.424
Looks good on you.

39:55.826 --> 39:57.761
Charlie: But the good news
is your daughter sassy

39:57.763 --> 40:00.930
And we can do
a bone-marrow transplant.

40:00.932 --> 40:04.401
I couldn't say no.

40:04.403 --> 40:06.002
You are the father
to my children.

40:06.004 --> 40:07.904
Thank you.

40:07.906 --> 40:09.873
Kevin has a good chance
of getting through this,

40:09.875 --> 40:12.742
But, um, he's gonna need
a lot of support.

40:14.979 --> 40:16.446
[ sighs ]

40:16.448 --> 40:17.747
I can be here on weekdays,
I guess.

40:17.749 --> 40:19.649
Thank you.
But I want a divorce.

40:19.651 --> 40:22.118
And I'm keeping the dogs because
I hate you and so do they.

40:22.120 --> 40:25.155
[ monitors beeping ]

40:25.157 --> 40:27.657
[ sighs ]

40:27.659 --> 40:29.559
[ andrew austin's
"sending out a message" plays ]

40:33.664 --> 40:34.964
Hey, arwen?

40:34.966 --> 40:36.132
Yes?

40:36.134 --> 40:38.435
¶ I close my eyes

40:38.437 --> 40:41.471
